{"title":"Ergon expands into all-road saddles with new foam-sandwich SR Allroad Core","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/09/28/ergon-expands-into-all-road-saddles-with-new-foam-sandwich-sr-allroad-core/","date":1632846075000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/22105547/SR_Allroad_F9Q7992-2-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/22105547/SR_Allroad_F9Q7992-2-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/22105547/SR_Allroad_F9Q7992-2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/22105547/SR_Allroad_F9Q7992-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/22105547/SR_Allroad_F9Q7992-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/22105547/SR_Allroad_F9Q7992-2.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-272417\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Ever since launching their Core construction method in 2017, Ergon has been steadily expanding their shock absorbing saddle range. Naturally, the all-road and gravel world are up next with the SR Allroad Core bringing those same benefits to the world of dropbars.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/22105549/SR_Allroad_Pro-Carbon_Fa%EF%BA%9F%E2%94%A4cher-e1632844981342.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/22105549/SR_Allroad_Pro-Carbon_Fa%EF%BA%9F%E2%94%A4cher-e1632844981342.jpg\" alt=\"SR Allroad Core saddle construction\" width=\"1155\" height=\"537\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/22105549/SR_Allroad_Pro-Carbon_Fa%EF%BA%9F%E2%94%A4cher-e1632844981342.jpg 1155w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/22105549/SR_Allroad_Pro-Carbon_Fa%EF%BA%9F%E2%94%A4cher-e1632844981342-297x138.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/22105549/SR_Allroad_Pro-Carbon_Fa%EF%BA%9F%E2%94%A4cher-e1632844981342-800x372.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/22105549/SR_Allroad_Pro-Carbon_Fa%EF%BA%9F%E2%94%A4cher-e1632844981342-120x56.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/22105549/SR_Allroad_Pro-Carbon_Fa%EF%BA%9F%E2%94%A4cher-e1632844981342-768x357.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1155px) 100vw, 1155px\"></a></p><p>The Core HD construction of the Allroad starts with a top layer of Orthopedic AirCell foam padding, then the “ergonomic Core” in the center of the saddle made from BASF’s Infinergy&nbsp; E-TPU/Closed Cell Particle Foam, and then a saddle shell and rails underneath. The sandwiched construction allows for the supportive foam padding needed for long rides while the ergonomic Core claims to filter out vibrations and shock, making for a more comfortable ride.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/28112557/Ergon-SR-Allroad-Core-gravel-saddle-with-foam-core-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/28112557/Ergon-SR-Allroad-Core-gravel-saddle-with-foam-core-2.jpg\" alt=\"SR Allroad Core saddle cover detail\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/28112557/Ergon-SR-Allroad-Core-gravel-saddle-with-foam-core-2.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/28112557/Ergon-SR-Allroad-Core-gravel-saddle-with-foam-core-2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/28112557/Ergon-SR-Allroad-Core-gravel-saddle-with-foam-core-2-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/28112557/Ergon-SR-Allroad-Core-gravel-saddle-with-foam-core-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/28112557/Ergon-SR-Allroad-Core-gravel-saddle-with-foam-core-2-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>Currently offered with a men’s specific Relief Channel, the gender-specific mention leads us to believe a women’s version is probably in the works. The saddle cover also features diagonal relief cuts which may improve grip in slippery conditions.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/22105521/Ergon-All-Road-Comp-Pro-Pro-Carbon-saddle-rails.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/22105521/Ergon-All-Road-Comp-Pro-Pro-Carbon-saddle-rails.jpg\" alt=\"SR Allroad Core saddle models\" width=\"1260\" height=\"1478\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/22105521/Ergon-All-Road-Comp-Pro-Pro-Carbon-saddle-rails.jpg 1260w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/22105521/Ergon-All-Road-Comp-Pro-Pro-Carbon-saddle-rails-256x300.jpg 256w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/22105521/Ergon-All-Road-Comp-Pro-Pro-Carbon-saddle-rails-800x938.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/22105521/Ergon-All-Road-Comp-Pro-Pro-Carbon-saddle-rails-102x120.jpg 102w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/22105521/Ergon-All-Road-Comp-Pro-Pro-Carbon-saddle-rails-768x901.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1260px) 100vw, 1260px\"></a></p><p>Offered in S/M for 9-12cm sit bone widths, and M/L for 12-16cm sit bone widths, the saddle will also come in three levels—the Comp, Pro, and Pro Carbon. Those models feature CroMo, TiNox, and carbon saddle rails respectively. The Comp is the only model with a nylon composite shell, the other two models use a carbon composite shell.</p><h2>Actual Weight &amp; Pricing</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/28112602/Ergon-SR-Allroad-Core-gravel-saddle-with-foam-core.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/28112602/Ergon-SR-Allroad-Core-gravel-saddle-with-foam-core.jpg\" alt=\"SR Allroad Core comp actual weight\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/28112602/Ergon-SR-Allroad-Core-gravel-saddle-with-foam-core.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/28112602/Ergon-SR-Allroad-Core-gravel-saddle-with-foam-core-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/28112602/Ergon-SR-Allroad-Core-gravel-saddle-with-foam-core-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/28112602/Ergon-SR-Allroad-Core-gravel-saddle-with-foam-core-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/28112602/Ergon-SR-Allroad-Core-gravel-saddle-with-foam-core-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>We got our hands on an SR Allroad Core Comp saddle in the M/L size, which weighed in at 268g—7g less than claimed. Expect this saddle to land State-side this coming Spring.</p><p><strong>SR Allroad Core Comp Men</strong><br>o Nylon Composite Shell<br>o CroMo-Rail<br>o $129.95<br>o Weight: S/M (260 g), M/L (275 g)<br><strong>SR Allroad Core Pro Men</strong><br>o Carbon Composite Shell<br>o TiNox Rail<br>o $149.95<br>o Weight: S/M (240 g), M/L (255 g)<br><strong>SR Allroad Core Pro Carbon Men</strong><br>o Carbon Composite Shell<br>o Carbon Rail<br>o $199.95<br>o Weight: S/M (195 g), M/L (210 g)</p><p><a href=\"https://www.ergonbike.com/en/product-details.html?anr=44063000&amp;s=srallroadcore&amp;a=saettel#info\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>ergonbike.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"114092517f8ad772a430e3c25f514eb5f839340100380f4c1263be711b4ab49f","category":"Cycling"}